        <h2 style="text-align:center;font-size: 22px;color:cyan;">Aloo Gobi</h2>
        <img style="padding-left:225px;width:400px;height:400px" src="https://static.toiimg.com/thumb/54693711.cms?imgsize=230683&width=800&height=800" alt="Aloo Gobi">
        <div id="en">
            <p style="color:#f1860b;font-size:15pt;font-weight:bold;">Ingredients:</p>

            <p style="color:#22facb;font-size:20px"> For the Aloo Gobi:</p>
            <ul style="list-style-type:circle">
                <li> 2 cups cauliflower florets (about half a medium-sized cauliflower)</li>
                <li> 2 medium-sized potatoes, peeled and diced into cubes</li>
                <li> 2 tablespoons cooking oil</li>
                <li> 1 teaspoon cumin seeds</li>
                <li> 1 onion, finely chopped</li>
                <li> 1 tomato, finely chopped</li>
                <li> 1-2 green chilies, slit (adjust to taste)</li>
                <li> 1 teaspoon ginger-garlic paste</li>
                <li> 1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder</li>
                <li> 1 teaspoon cumin powder</li>
                <li> 1 teaspoon coriander powder</li>
                <li> 1/2 teaspoon red chili powder (adjust to taste)</li>
                <li> Salt to taste</li>
                <li> Fresh coriander leaves for garnish</li>
            </ul>
            <p style="color:#f1860b;font-size:15pt;font-weight:bold;">Instructions:</p>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">1. Prep the Vegetables:</li><ul>
                <li> Clean the cauliflower and cut it into small florets.</li>
                <li> Peel and dice the potatoes into cubes. </li>
                <li> Rinse them under cold water to remove excess starch.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">2. Sauté the Vegetables:</li><ul>
                <li> Heat oil in a large pan or skillet over medium heat.</li>
                <li> Add cumin seeds and let them splutter.</li>
                <li> Add finely chopped onions and green chilies. </li>
                <li> Sauté until the onions become translucent.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">3. Add Ginger-Garlic Paste and Spices:</li><ul>
                <li> Add ginger-garlic paste and sauté for a couple of minutes until the raw smell disappears.</li>
                <li> Add turmeric powder, cumin powder, coriander powder, and red chili powder.</li>
                <li> Stir well and cook for a few minutes until the spices are fragrant.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">4. Add Tomatoes:</li><ul>
                <li> Add the finely chopped tomatoes and cook until they become soft and the oil starts to separate from the mixture.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">5. Add Potatoes and Cauliflower:</li><ul>
                <li> Add the diced potatoes and cauliflower florets to the pan.</li>
                <li> Mix them with the onion-tomato mixture.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">6. Cook the Aloo Gobi:</li><ul>
                <li> Season with salt to taste and stir to coat the vegetables with the spices.</li>
                <li> Cover the pan and let the Aloo Gobi cook over low to medium heat. </li>
                <li> Stir occasionally to ensure even cooking.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">7. Check Doneness:</li><ul>
                <li> Cook until the potatoes and cauliflower are tender but not mushy. This may take about 15-20 minutes.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">8. Garnish and Serve:</li><ul>
                <li> Once the Aloo Gobi is cooked, garnish with fresh coriander leaves.</li>
                <li> Serve hot with roti, naan, or steamed rice.</li>

            </ul><p style="color:orange;font-size:20px">Enjoy your homemade Aloo Gobi, a delicious and comforting vegetarian dish!</p>
